  "local_port": 35316,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to register a startup company for \"Startup India\" campaign and how much will it benefit a startup?",
  "response": "The Startup India campaign is a flagship initiative of the Government of India that aims to build a strong ecosystem for nurturing innovation and startups in the country. The campaign offers various benefits and incentives to startups recognized by the Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT). Here\u2019s the procedure to register a startup under the Startup India campaign and the benefits it offers:\n\n---\n\n### **Procedure to Register a Startup under Startup India**\n\n1. **Incorporate Your Business**  \n   - First, incorporate your business as a Private Limited Company, Limited Liability Partnership (LLP), or Partnership Firm.  \n   - Register your business with the Registrar of Companies (RoC) or Registrar of Firms.\n\n2. **Register on the Startup India Portal**  \n   - Visit the [Startup India website](https://www.startupindia.gov.in).  \n   - Create an account and fill out the registration form with details of your business.\n\n3. **Provide Required Documents**  \n   - Certificate of Incorporation/Registration.  \n   - Authorized representative\u2019s details (e.g., PAN, Aadhaar).  \n   - Brief description of the business and its innovative nature.  \n   - Details of patents or trademarks (if applicable).  \n   - Letter of recommendation or funding details (optional but can strengthen the application).\n\n4. **Self-Certification**  \n   - Declare that your business meets the following criteria:  \n     - It is less than 10 years old.  \n     - Its annual turnover does not exceed \u20b9100 crore in any financial year.  \n     - It is working towards innovation, development, or improvement of products, processes, or services.  \n     - It is not formed by splitting or reconstructing an existing business.  \n\n5. **Apply for Recognition**  \n   - Submit the application online.  \n   - Once verified, you will receive a **Recognition Number**.  \n\n6. **Obtain the Certificate of Recognition**  \n   - After successful verification, you will receive a Certificate of Recognition as a DPIIT-recognized startup.  \n\n---\n\n### **Benefits of Registering under Startup India**\n\n1. **Tax Exemptions**  \n   - Startups recognized by DPIIT are eligible for a **tax holiday for 3 consecutive years** in a block of 7 years.  \n   - Exemption from tax on investments above the fair market value (Section 56(2)(viib) of Income Tax Act).\n\n2. **Simplified Compliance**  \n   - Self-certification under labor and environmental laws.  \n   - Reduced compliance burden for startups.\n\n3. **Access to Funding**  \n   - Access to the **\u20b910,000 crore Startup India Fund of Funds** managed by SIDBI for investments in startups.  \n   - Easier access to venture capital and angel investors.\n\n4. **Intellectual Property Rights (IPR) Support**  \n   - Fast-tracking of patent applications.  \n   - 80% rebate on patent filing fees and 50% rebate on trademark filing fees.\n\n5. **Networking and Mentorship**  \n   - Access to Startup India Hub for guidance and mentorship.  \n   - Participation in government programs and events.\n\n6. **Public Procurement**  \n   - Startups are exempted from prior experience and turnover criteria for government tenders.  \n\n7. **Ease of Winding Up**  \n   - Startups can wind up operations within 90 days under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016.\n\n8. **Other Benefits**  \n   - Subsidies on incubator facilities.  \n   - Networking opportunities with investors and industry experts.  \n\n---\n\n### **Conclusion**  \nRegistering under Startup India provides significant financial and regulatory benefits, making it easier for startups to scale and succeed. By reducing compliance burdens, offering tax exemptions, and facilitating funding, the initiative fosters a conducive environment for innovation and entrepreneurship in India.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
